<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8">
		<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
		<title>Filmstagram</title>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/stylesheets/about.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Cookie&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
		<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/modernizr/2.8.3/modernizr.min.js" type="text/javascript" async></script>
	</head>
	<body>


		<div class="video-container">

		  <video autoplay loop>
		    <source src="videos/film.mp4" type="video/mp4">
		  </video>

		  <div class="overlay mx-auto">

				<div class="card">
	        <div class="card-body">
	  				<p class="card-text text-dark text-center" style='font-size: .85rem;'>
	            <span style="font-family: 'Cookie', cursive; font-size: 1.3rem;">Filmstagram</span> is my first solo-project,
							created with the intention of refining my understanding and implementation of RESTful routing and front-end
							web design.
						</p>
						<p id='expl' class="card-text text-dark" style='font-size: .85rem;'>
							This app has most of the same functionality as the website after which it is modeled, Instagram.
							Users can create, edit, and delete their own posts, along with leave comments on both their own
							publications as well as those of other users. This application was created using the Node.js
							JavaScript run-time environment and contains more than 1,200 lines of code spread across roughly
							14 different HTML, CSS, EJS, and JS files.
						</p>
						<hr>
						<p class="card-text text-dark mb-1" style='font-size: .85rem;'>
							The following NPM-installed packages, among others, allow for the
							functionality of the application:
						</p>
						<div class="container">
							<ul class="text-dark list-group list-group-flush" style='font-size: .85rem;'>
								<li class="list-group-item">
									Request, which provides access to the <a href='http://omdbapi.com/'>OMDb API</a>
									and gives the user search capabilities
								</li>
								<li class="list-group-item">
									Mongoose, which facilitates MongoDB object modeling
								</li>
								<li class="list-group-item">
									Passport, for authenticating users and requests
								</li>
								<li class="list-group-item">
									Express-session, which allows sessions to identify users across requests
								</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
	        </div>
	        <a id='back-btn' href="/movies" class="btn btn-dark mb-2 mx-auto">Back</a>
				</div>


		  </div>

		</div>

		<script>

		</script>
	</body>
</html>
